[These reports are fragmentary and rapidly overtaken by the release of new data. As of 9 Apr 2013 the number of cases has increased to 28 with 9 fatalities. Most of the cases/fatalities are middle-aged or elderly. A mild infection has been reported in the case of one child. There is still no confirmation of human-to-human transmission of infection, and all cases are still confined to the eastern coastal region in and around Shanghai. - Mod.CP]
